eptional resource completion.  Honored with the title of Best Execution, Safety, and Quality Conscious Engineer in MP state for the ISP Kalisindh Mlis Phase-1  Directed the Laying of 22 kilometers of MS pipeline with diameters of 2.1 meters and 980mm, including conducting hydrostatic tests to validate pipeline integrity and compliance with safety standards.  Reviewed detailed project blueprints and performed on-site evaluations to ensure all pre-construction conditions met  Performed specific soil stability tests to confirm ground suitability along the pipeline path, ensuring a stable foundation for installation.  Managed the project timeline meticulously, reallocating resources dynamically to avoid any delays and ensure timely completion.  Negotiated with local government officials to arrange necessary road closures and traffic diversions, minimizing disruption to local communities during pipeline laying.  Ensured rigorous adherence to documentation standards, keeping all project records accurate and compliant with regulatory requirements. | Third Party: WAPCOS; Execution Engineer; MEIL Constructions | 2016-2018 || Mega Lift Irrigation Projects at Cluster-6 | Odisha, India  Spearheaded the Laying of MS, DI, and HDPE pipelines over a 50 kms network, conducting hydrostatic testing to verify pipeline integrity and adherence to safety protocols.  Successfully completed the construction and commissioning of wall erections and outlet chambers, ensuring operational readiness.  Implemented advanced sensor technology across the irrigation system to facilitate real-time monitoring and streamline operating and maintenance procedures.  Led community outreach initiatives to maintain transparent communication with local populations impacted by the construction, enhancing community relations and project acceptance.  Applied innovative fabrication techniques to improve the longevity and reliability of pipeline materials.  Coordinated logistics with suppliers to guaran